CoinFlipCode.ipynb — A PyTorch implementation of a learned Markov Chain model for coin flip sequences. It generates training data where heads follows heads 90% of the time, then trains an embedding-based model to recover those transition probabilities. The model successfully learns the bias, outputting ~0.89 P(heads|heads) and ~0.12 P(heads|tails).
SimpleCoinFlipApril1.ipynb — A beginner-friendly autoregressive coin flip predictor using a small feedforward neural network. Given a history of 4 past flips, it predicts the probability of the next flip being heads. Trained on 8 hand-labeled sequences, it achieves near-perfect predictions on the training data.
Together, these notebooks explore how neural networks can learn sequential patterns in coin flip data, progressing from a simple Markov model to a small autoregressive network.
